It is intended solely as an overview of existing knowledge, as an educational tool, and as a guide to support discussions on where additional geologic mapping might be needed. Because of its generalized unit descriptions, regional scale, and incomplete integration across the map area (as discussed in Soller and Reheis, 2004), this map is not intended to be used at a larger (greater detail) scale than 1:5,000,000.</idAbs> <searchKeys> <keyword>Geoscientific Information</keyword> <keyword>Geology</keyword> <keyword>Surficial materials</keyword> </searchKeys> <idPurp>Surficial Materials in the Conterminous United States</idPurp> <idCredit>U.S. Geological Survey Soller, D.R., Reheis, M.C., Garrity, C.P., Van Sistine, D.R. </idCredit> <resConst> <Consts> <useLimit>This digital publication was prepared by an agency of the United States Government.
